# Review — persona: trader / step: verify / mode: enterprise

_End-user trader running the EA on a live or demo account._

## Questions

- [ ] **trader-01** (critical) — What is the maximum acceptable drawdown for this strategy?
- [ ] **trader-02** (critical) — What instruments and timeframes is this EA approved to trade?
- [ ] **trader-03** (critical) — What is the per-trade risk percentage and how is it enforced?
- [ ] **trader-04** (critical) — Is there a daily-loss kill switch and when does it fire?
- [ ] **trader-05** (critical) — Does the EA respect news windows / session boundaries?
- [ ] **trader-06** (high) — How will I know the EA is functioning (journal cues, dashboard, alerts)?
- [ ] **trader-07** (high) — What happens to open positions if the EA is detached or restarts?
- [ ] **trader-08** (high) — Is there a manual override and how do I trigger it safely?
- [ ] **trader-09** (high) — What is the expected number of trades per day / week?
- [ ] **trader-10** (high) — What spread / commission environment is the strategy tuned for?
- [ ] **trader-11** (high) — How is leverage selected and constrained?
- [ ] **trader-12** (high) — Does the EA handle weekend gap risk explicitly?
- [ ] **trader-13** (standard) — What evidence supports the claimed expectancy (sample size, time span)?
- [ ] **trader-14** (standard) — How are losing streaks bounded behaviourally (rule, not feeling)?
- [ ] **trader-15** (standard) — What is the worst historical drawdown sequence and recovery time?
- [ ] **trader-16** (standard) — Are trade reasons logged in a human-readable form?
- [ ] **trader-17** (standard) — What is the rollback procedure if a release misbehaves?
- [ ] **trader-18** (standard) — How is performance reported back to me (daily, weekly, ad-hoc)?
- [ ] **trader-19** (standard) — What's the policy if a broker changes execution rules mid-run?
- [ ] **trader-20** (standard) — Are my expectations on uptime aligned with the chosen hosting?
- [ ] **trader-21** (standard) — How is success/failure of a trade communicated post-mortem?
- [ ] **trader-22** (standard) — What position sizing rule applies for compounding vs fixed?
- [ ] **trader-23** (standard) — Are entry/exit signals deterministic given identical input bars?
- [ ] **trader-24** (standard) — Have I personally validated the EA on demo for at least 2 weeks?
- [ ] **trader-25** (standard) — Do I understand all configurable inputs and their failure modes?

## Step template

# Step 7 / 8 — VERIFY

Run every external gate the kit ships and capture the artefacts.

## Inputs
- `step-6-build.md`
- Demo broker credentials (multi-broker step)

## Activities
- [ ] `mql5-lint` — 8 critical AP must pass
- [ ] `mql5-compile` — 0 errors required (warnings allowed)
- [ ] `mql5-backtest` — produce tester XML
- [ ] `mql5-walkforward` — IS/OOS correlation ≥ 0.5
- [ ] `mql5-monte-carlo` — 95th-pct DD ≤ 1.5× reported
- [ ] `mql5-overfit-check` — OOS/IS Sharpe ratio ≥ 0.7
- [ ] `mql5-multibroker` — protocol B-1/B-2/B-3 pass
- [ ] `mql5-trader-check` — ≥ 15/17 personal, 17/17 enterprise
- [ ] `mql5-rri-bt` — backtest review with 5 personas

## Outputs
- `step-7-verify.md` — pass/fail per gate, links to artefact files

## Exit criteria
- Every required gate green
- 64-cell matrix ≥ 56 PASS (enterprise)

> Sentinel: `touch .rri-state/verify.done`.
